ults using metrics such as accuracy, robustness, and interpretability. The expected outcomes include a more robust and accurate graph learning framework that can handle noisy and sparse data effectively.\n\n**Methodology:**\n- **Data Collection:** Gather a dataset with both explicit graph structures and textual data associated with nodes. This dataset will be used to train and evaluate the GraphEdit model.\n- **Model Development:** Develop the GraphEdit model, which combines GNNs and LLMs. The GNN will process the graph structure, while the LLM will process the textual data. The outputs from both models will be integrated to refine the graph structure.\n- **Training and Evaluation:** Train the GraphEdit model on the dataset and evaluate its performance using metrics such as accuracy, robustness, and interpretability. The model will be tested on both synthetic and real-world datasets to ensure its effectiveness.\n\n**Expected Outcomes:**\n- A more robust and accurate graph learning framework that can handle noisy and sparse data effectively.\n- Improved performance in downstream tasks, such as node classification and link prediction.\n- A deeper understanding of the integration of textual data into graph learning processes.\n\n**Timeline:**\n- **Month 1-2:** Data collection and preprocessing.\n- **Month 3-4:** Model development and initial training.\n- **Month 5-6:** Model evaluation and refinement.\n- **Month 7-8:** Final testing and documentation.\n- **Month 9:** Preparation for presentation or submission.\n\n**Resources:**\n- Computational resources for training and evaluating the model.\n- Datasets with both explicit graph structures and textual data.\n- Funding for research activities and resources.\n\n### Next Steps\n- Share the draft of the research proposal with peers or mentors for feedback.\n- Incorporate any suggestions or criticisms to improve the proposal.\n- Format the proposal according to the guidelines of the intended audience.\n- Prepare a presentation or summary if the proposal needs to be presented to a team or stakeholders.\n- Secure necessary resources for the research project.\n\nThis refined proposal is now ready for further feedback and finalization."}

