sionality of textual data.\n\n**[Question 4] - Why hasn't it been solved before?**\nPrevious research has focused on explicit graph structures and has not fully leveraged the potential of textual data. The integration of LLMs into GSL is a relatively new and unexplored area, requiring novel methodologies and techniques.\n\n**[Question 5] - What are the key components of my approach and results?**\nThe proposed methodology involves developing a model called GraphEdit that uses LLMs to generate embeddings for node attributes and incorporates these embeddings into GNNs. The model will be evaluated on various datasets with noisy and sparse graph structures, using metrics such as accuracy, robustness, and interpretability to measure its performance. Expected outcomes include a more robust and accurate GNN that can handle real-world data imperfections.\n\n### Next Steps:\n- **Refine the Methodology:** Provide more detailed steps and algorithms.\n- **Select and Describe Datasets:** Choose and describe the datasets that will be used.\n- **Define Evaluation Metrics:** Clearly define the metrics for evaluating the model.\n- **Conduct Preliminary Experiments:** Plan and conduct preliminary experiments.\n- **Draft the Proposal:** Write a detailed research proposal.\n\nBy following these steps, you can ensure that the research proposal is comprehensive, well-articulated, and ready for further development or submission."}, 'task_results': [{'agent1': "Result from the model:To refine and finalize the research proposal, I will follow the outlined steps:\n\n1. **Refine the Research Proposal:**\n   - Ensure that each of the five core questions is clearly and concisely answered.\n   - Provide more detail on the methodology, including specific techniques and tools that will be used.\n   - Clarify the expected outcomes and how they will be measured.\n\n2. **Seek Feedback:**\n   - Share the draft of the research proposal with peers or mentors for feedback.\n   - Incorporate any suggestio